longBusinessSummary: HearAtLast Holdings, Inc. operates hearing clinics in North America. The company offers hearing assessments and hearing instruments. Its products comprise digital hearing aid instruments and assistive-listening devices, as well as accessories, such as hearing aid wax guards, chargers, cleaners, sound tubes, etc. As of March 31, 2010, HearAtLast Holdings, Inc. had 23 hearing aid clinics within the Wal-Mart structure. The company was formerly known as 226 Music Group, Inc. and changed its name to HearAtLast Holdings, Inc. in 2007. HearAtLast Holdings, Inc. was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Georgetown, Canada.
